/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/thermal-time/tth-deltaK-and-period-shift.md:90:**Recommended figure of merit:** The L² norm ‖C_full − C_local‖/‖C_full‖ = 0.827 (82.7%) at λ=0.3 is the more reliable discriminant — it captures the full structural difference (single-frequency TTH vs. two-frequency beating QM). The zero-crossing metric understates the discrepancy.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/thermal-time/tth-deltaK-and-period-shift.md:94:With the correct normalization (τ=β·t), TTH makes a genuinely different prediction from standard QM for entangled systems. However, the relevant figure of merit is not the period shift (which compared against the free oscillator baseline) but the L² norm discrepancy between C_local_TTH and C_full_QM (82.7% at λ=0.3). The structural source of this discrepancy: C_full has two-frequency normal-mode beating, C_local has one frequency. No parameter tuning can fix this structural mismatch. See `tth-full-qm-vs-local-tth.md` for the complete comparison.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-atlas-exact-ns-tiny-trigger-firewall-missionary.log:864:../../agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-003-thermal-time-learnings.md:22:2. **The Gaussian caveat resolution design (coherent + squeezed two-tier) was excellent.** Coherent state = trivial validation (δC_local = constant, analytically predictable). Squeezed state = real test (Gaussian-exact, but non-trivial modular Hamiltonian). This two-tier design caught potential code errors early and then produced the decisive result.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/thermal-time/INDEX.md:13:- **tth-full-qm-vs-local-tth.md** — Direct comparison C_full_QM (H_AB evolution) vs. C_local_TTH (K_A/β evolution). Control check C_global = C_full at machine zero confirms K_AB = βH_AB. Main result: STRUCTURAL discrepancy — C_full has two-frequency normal-mode beating at ω_± = √(ω²±λ), C_local has single frequency ω_eff < ω_A (no beating). L² discrepancy: 9.1% (λ=0.1), 82.7% (λ=0.3), >100% (λ=0.5). Not fixable by parameter tuning. Two TTH interpretations: global TTH (K_AB) ≡ QM by construction; local TTH (K_A) ≠ QM structurally. Best discriminant: ‖C_full − C_local‖/‖C_full‖ (not period shift). Verified: Fock truncation convergence 1 ppb (N=15→N=20).
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/thermal-time/INDEX.md:17:- **nonequilibrium-tth-post-quench.md** — Non-equilibrium TTH test: post-quench state (thermal state of uncoupled system under coupled dynamics). TTH ≠ QM for all λ>0 (102% at λ=0.3, 174% at λ=0.5). Discrepancy is STRUCTURAL: C_QM has coupled normal-mode frequencies ω_±, C_global has only uncoupled ω — completely disjoint spectra. Modular time = pre-quench time (K encodes preparation Hamiltonian). Product-state identity: C_global = C_local exactly for product states. Squeezed state contrast: global TTH 7.8% (quantitative, correct frequencies) vs. 102% post-quench (structural, wrong frequencies). Exact analytical formulas verified to 3e-13.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/thermal-time/INDEX.md:21:- **gaussian-caveat-resolution.md** — Resolves the Gaussian approximation caveat on the excited-state finding. Squeezed vacuum S_m(r)|0> — a Gaussian state where the modular Hamiltonian is EXACT — reproduces the same structural mismatch: modular flow at modular frequencies, physical frequency absent. Discrepancy grows as N^{0.44} (up to N=400). Coherent state control confirms pipeline (delta_C_local = constant to machine precision). Squeezing parameter sweep shows mismatch is structural, independent of squeezing strength (discrepancy 13-66 across r=0.1 to 1.0). Physical interpretation: boost vs. translation symmetries are fundamentally different.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/agents/library/factual/thermal-time/tth-full-qm-vs-local-tth.md:10:Direct comparison of C_full_QM (standard QM, full H_AB dynamics) against C_local_TTH (local TTH, K_A/β generator). Result: the discrepancy is **structural, not quantitative** — C_full has two-frequency normal-mode beating while C_local has a single frequency. L² norm discrepancy: 9.1% (λ=0.1), 82.7% (λ=0.3), >100% (λ=0.5). Control check C_global = C_full at machine zero confirms K_AB/β = H_AB for Gibbs states. The key theoretical interpretation: TTH at global level ≡ QM (trivially); TTH at local level ≠ QM and misses the normal-mode structure of coupled systems.
