# Exploration 002 Summary

## Goal

Decide whether the frozen pair `(C_ℓ, E_ℓ^transfer)` survives the smallest
honest exact-support audit, or whether the minimal setting already shows
model-level failure.

## What I tried

- Wrote the explicit transfer identity for `C_ℓ`.
- Checked the single-triad case first.
- Built the smallest exact-helical cluster with two distinct transfer inputs
  feeding the same receiver mode.
- Computed exact helical coefficients and an explicit phase/amplitude family
  using `code/minimal_cluster_cancellation_demo.py`.

